=Go through this email summary and identify all key details mentioned, any specific issues to look at, and action items.
Use this format to output

Clean the following JSON string by:
Removing the triple backticks (``` and ```json)
Replacing all \n escape characters with actual newlines
Unescaping it so it becomes valid, formatted JSON
Output only the cleaned, pretty-printed JSON

{
 "summary_of_emails": [
 "Point 1",
 "Point 2",
 "Point 3"
 ],
 "actions": [
 {
 "name": "Name 1",
 "action": "Action 1"
 },
 {
 "name": "Name 1",
 "action": "Action 2"
 },
 {
 "name": "Name 2",
 "action": "Action 3"
 }
 ]
}

Input Data:

 {{ $json.data.toJsonString() }}

parameters.jsCode:
const rawString = $input.first().json.text;

// Step 1: Remove the ```json and ``` markers
const noCodeBlock = rawString.replace(/```json|```/g, '');

// Step 2: Replace all \n with real newlines (optional for readability)
const unescapedNewlines = noCodeBlock.replace(/\\n/g, '\n');

// Step 3: Parse the string as JSON (if needed, trim spaces first)
try {
  const jsonObject = JSON.parse(unescapedNewlines.trim());
  return jsonObject;
} catch (e) {
  console.error('Failed to parse JSON:', e.message);
}
